## 3. Callback: create session, redirect to sales points

```java
@GetMapping("/auth/callback")
public void callback(
        @RequestParam String code,
        @RequestParam String state,
        HttpServletResponse response
) throws IOException {

    String sessionId = authService.handleCallback(code, state);

    Cookie cookie = new Cookie("ARTHUR_SESSION", sessionId);
    cookie.setHttpOnly(true);
    cookie.setSecure(false); // true in prod
    cookie.setPath("/");
    cookie.setMaxAge(3600);

    response.addCookie(cookie);
    response.sendRedirect("/arthur-core/sales-points");
}
```

## 4. `handleCallback`

```java
public String handleCallback(String code, String state) {
    AuthTransaction tx = redisAuthTransactionService.findByState(state);

    AppConfigResponse appConfig = lancelotClient.getApp(tx.getAppId());

    Map<String, Object> tokenResponse = exchangeToken(code, tx, appConfig);

    String idToken = (String) tokenResponse.get("id_token");

    JwtUserClaims claims = jwtService.extractClaims(idToken);

    String userId = claims.getPreferredUsername();

    UserResponse user = lancelotClient.getUserById(userId);

    UserSession session = new UserSession();
    session.setSessionId(UUID.randomUUID().toString());
    session.setAppId(tx.getAppId());
    session.setUserId(user.getUserId());
    session.setUsername(user.getUsername());
    session.setRoles(user.getRoles());
    session.setSalesPoints(user.getSalesPoints());
    session.setCreatedAt(Instant.now());

    redisSessionService.save(session);
    redisAuthTransactionService.delete(state);

    return session.getSessionId();
}
```

