## 10. Exchange service

```java
public HandoffExchangeResponse exchange(String code) {
    LoginHandoff handoff = redisLoginHandoffService.findByCode(code);

    if (handoff == null) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid or expired handoff code");
    }

    if (Instant.now().isAfter(handoff.getExpiresAt())) {
        redisLoginHandoffService.delete(code);
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Expired handoff code");
    }

    UserSession session = redisSessionService.findBySessionId(handoff.getSessionId());

    redisLoginHandoffService.delete(code);

    HandoffExchangeResponse response = new HandoffExchangeResponse();
    response.setUserId(session.getUserId());
    response.setUsername(session.getUsername());
    response.setRoles(session.getRoles());
    response.setAppId(session.getAppId());
    response.setSelectedSalesPointId(session.getSelectedSalesPointId());

    return response;
}
```

## 11. Redis handoff service

```java
@Service
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class RedisLoginHandoffService {

    private static final String PREFIX = "handoff:";

    private final RedisTemplate<String, Object> redisTemplate;
    private final ObjectMapper objectMapper;

    public void save(LoginHandoff handoff) {
        redisTemplate.opsForValue().set(
                PREFIX + handoff.getCode(),
                handoff,
                Duration.ofSeconds(60)
        );
    }

    public LoginHandoff findByCode(String code) {
        Object value = redisTemplate.opsForValue().get(PREFIX + code);

        if (value == null) {
            return null;
        }

        if (value instanceof LoginHandoff handoff) {
            return handoff;
        }

        return objectMapper.convertValue(value, LoginHandoff.class);
    }

    public void delete(String code) {
        redisTemplate.delete(PREFIX + code);
    }
}
```

That gives you the exact flow:

```text
callback → session
sales point select → handoff
B2Boost → exchange code
```
