Use **Thymeleaf** for now.

It is the simplest because the sales point screen belongs to **Arthur Core**, not B2Boost.

Add dependency:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-thymeleaf</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

Create:

```text
src/main/resources/templates/sales-points.html
```

Example:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns:th="http://www.thymeleaf.org">
<head>
    <title>Select Sales Point</title>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Select Sales Point</h2>

<form method="post" action="/arthur-core/sales-points/select">
    <div th:each="sp : ${salesPoints}">
        <label>
            <input type="radio" name="salesPointId" th:value="${sp.id}" required>
            <span th:text="${sp.name}">Sales Point</span>
        </label>
        <br>
    </div>

    <button type="submit">Confirm</button>
</form>

</body>
</html>
```

